</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="393" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,1837,2008]" pageId="20" pageNumber="393">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,400,1837,1863]" pageId="20" pageNumber="393">Materials examined.</emphasis>
16 individuals; Stations Vas. 5(1), 10(1), 18(1), 20(3), 23(1), 24(1), 25(2), 26(4), 30(1), 36(1).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="393" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,1837,2008]" pageId="20" pageNumber="393">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,305,1909,1935]" pageId="20" pageNumber="393">Distribution.</emphasis>
Atlanto-Mediterranean (
<bibRefCitation author="Bellan-Santini, D. &amp; Ruffo, S." box="[589,930,1909,1935]" pageId="20" pageNumber="393" pagination="273 - 292" refId="ref18519" refString="Bellan-Santini, D. &amp; Ruffo, S. (2003) Biogeography of benthic marine amphipods in Mediterranean Sea. Biogeographia-The Journal of Integrative Biogeography, 24 (1), 273 - 292. https: // doi. org / 10.21426 / B 6110176" type="journal article" year="2003">Bellan-Santini &amp; Ruffo 2003</bibRefCitation>
). The species was reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[1317,1398,1909,1935]" name="Cyprus" pageId="20" pageNumber="393">Cyprus</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kocatas, A. &amp; Katagan, T." box="[198,436,1945,1972]" pageId="20" pageNumber="393" pagination="147 - 160" refId="ref20983" refString="Kocatas, A., Katagan, T. &amp; Huseyin. A. B. (2001) Contribution to the knowledge of the crustacean fauna of Cyprus. Israel Journal of Zoology, 47 (2), 147 - 160. https: // doi. org / 10.1560 / YQL 8 - 4 PBT- 12 W 2 - 82 HV" type="journal article" year="2001">
Kocatas 
<emphasis box="[295,351,1945,1971]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="393">et al.</emphasis>
(2001)
</bibRefCitation>
. In Vasiliko Bay (current study), it is considered as a rare species (FI: 23.8 %).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="394" pageId="20" pageNumber="393" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,1837,2008]" lastBlockId="21.[198,1437,150,357]" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="394" pageId="20" pageNumber="393">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,252,1981,2007]" pageId="20" pageNumber="393">Ecology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Montagu" baseAuthorityYear="1808" box="[261,485,1981,2007]" class="Malacostraca" family="Phliantidae" genus="Pereionotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="testudo">
<emphasis box="[261,485,1981,2007]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="393">Pereionotus testudo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found in association with algae, on rocks and stones and on soft-bottom sedi-ments (mud, mud and sand mixture) at 
<quantity box="[653,740,150,177]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.65" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="0.3" pageId="21" pageNumber="394" unit="m" value="36.5" valueMax="70.0" valueMin="3.0">3–70 m</quantity>
depth (
<bibRefCitation author="Kocatas, A. &amp; Katagan, T." box="[828,1056,150,176]" pageId="21" pageNumber="394" pagination="147 - 160" refId="ref20983" refString="Kocatas, A., Katagan, T. &amp; Huseyin. A. B. (2001) Contribution to the knowledge of the crustacean fauna of Cyprus. Israel Journal of Zoology, 47 (2), 147 - 160. https: // doi. org / 10.1560 / YQL 8 - 4 PBT- 12 W 2 - 82 HV" type="journal article" year="2001">
Kocatas 
<emphasis box="[929,987,150,176]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="394">et al.</emphasis>
2001
</bibRefCitation>
). In Vasiliko Bay it was found at depths of 
<quantity box="[311,411,186,213]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" metricValueMax="5.9" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="21" pageNumber="394" unit="m" value="36.0" valueMax="59.0" valueMin="13.0">13–59 m</quantity>
(34 + 
<quantity box="[489,550,186,213]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="21" pageNumber="394" unit="m" value="14.0">14 m</quantity>
), mainly in muddy sand and also sand substrates, with organic matter ranging between 
<geoCoordinate box="[298,360,222,248]" degrees="3.179" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="21" pageNumber="394" precision="55" value="3.179">3.179</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[361,438,222,248]" degrees="9.414" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="21" pageNumber="394" precision="55" value="-9.414">–9.414</geoCoordinate>
% (6.012 + 1.617 %) and in association with 
<emphasis box="[951,1389,222,249]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="394">
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. V. Lamouroux" authorityYear="1809" baseAuthorityName="Forsskal" box="[951,1086,222,249]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Caulerpaceae" genus="Caulerpa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Bryopsidales" pageId="21" pageNumber="394" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="prolifera">C. prolifera</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sonder" authorityYear="1845" box="[1096,1264,222,249]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Caulerpaceae" genus="Caulerpa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Bryopsidales" pageId="21" pageNumber="394" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="cylindracea">C. cylindracea</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ascherson" authorityYear="1870" baseAuthorityName="Ucria" box="[1275,1389,222,249]" class="Liliopsida" family="Cymodoceaceae" genus="Cymodocea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alismatales" pageId="21" pageNumber="394" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nodosa">C. nodosa</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[198,344,259,285]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Dictyotaceae" genus="Dictyota" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dictyotales" pageId="21" pageNumber="377" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="spp">
<emphasis box="[198,294,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="394">Dictyota</emphasis>
spp
</taxonomicName>
. It was found in stations classified according to the Bentix Index as in: “high” (1 station, 1 individual), “good” (5 stations, 8 individuals) and “moderate” (4 stations, 7 individuals). It was recorded at a fish farm station (1 individual) and at the buoy (2 individuals).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
